<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:25:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T18:26:00-05:00" n="933" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d933">
                    <head>Inhabitants of Franches Montagnes</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Franches Montagnes</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:34" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:34">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">District of Franches Montagnes</hi>.</p>
                    <p>Signatures to the Berne address of sympathy to the people of the American
                        Union, congratulating them on the victorious restoration of their
                        government, and condoling with them on the loss of Abraham Lincoln, their
                        savior.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>KATMANN, <hi rend="italic">Prefect</hi>.</item>
                                <item>E. BROSSARD, <hi rend="italic">Judge</hi>.</item>
                                <item>General QUELAIN.</item>
                                <item>Lieutenant HUSSBAUMER.</item>
                                <item>Captain HENNIN.</item>
                                <item>Captain GIRARD.<lb/>And forty-two others.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>